frameDefinitions: Two parties, the Exchangers, each give and receive from the other Themes.
An Obstruction blocks an Eclipsed entity partially or completely from view.
An Agent has placed a Theme in an accessible but somewhat out of the way Location for the purposes of maintaining it free from harm and illegitimate use while it is not being used.
The Quantity of a Collection occurring in a Place has a particular Measure, which is related to the amount generally needed.
In this frame an Agent continues to possess a Theme for a Duration of time. '' 'In her heart she must retain bitterness against those who had killed him.'
A Person takes leave from his or her routine Activity (such as work or school) for a Duration of time.
frameExamples: They <t>swapped</t> the island with the Neapolitan government of the day for the much smaller Capri.
A small green bulb <t>concealed</t> behind the panel flashed on momentarily .
There is evidence that volatile materials have always been <t>scarce</t> on the Moon .
In her heart she must <t>retain</t> bitterness against those who had killed him.
The claimant should then submit medical certificates for the duration of their <t>absence</t> from work.INI
listRoleDefinitions:
In cases where the <fen>Exchangers</fen> involved in a conversation are
construed as two separate groups with different levels of
volitionality or control, this role identifies the conversational
participant with greater semantic and syntactic prominence, as
compared with <fen>Exchanger_2</fen>. That is, <fen>Exchanger_1</fen> is generally
encoded as Subject, and peripheral FEs that do not make reference
to the event itself generally make reference to <fen>Exchanger_1</fen>. Thus
a <fen>Purpose</fen> (or <fen>Means</fen>, <fen>Depictive</fen>, or <fen>Manner</fen>) is construed to be that
of <fen>Exchanger_1</fen>, not necessarily that of <fen>Exchanger_2</fen> or the group
of <fen>Exchangers</fen> as a whole.

In cases where the <fen>Exchangers</fen> involved in a conversation are
construed as two separate groups with different levels of
volitionality or control, <fen>Exchanger_2</fen> refers to the semantically
and grammatically less prominent group. It is generally encoded
within a prepositional phrase (e.g. headed by with). Note that it
is possible for a single role to correspond to multiple referents.
For example, if the prepositional object in the example below were
plural, we would still assign it the single role <fen>Exchanger_2</fen>.

In some sentences both participants are expressed by the Subject, and there is no 'with'-phrase (cf example 1). In sentences like this, the Subject is assigned the role role <fen>Exchangers</fen>. In such sentences, the Subject always denotes more than one person, and it is understood that the reciprocal communication takes place between these two (or more) people. The Subject may denote two or more people either through conjunction, as in example 1, or through plurality, as in example 2, or by denoting a group, as in example 3. In each of these cases the role <fen>Exchangers</fen> is assigned. Notice that for nouns in the Exchange frame, it is possible for the <fen>Exchangers</fen> role to be expressed by a prepositional phrase as in example 4.
The item that begins in the possession of <fen>Exchanger_1</fen>.
The item that begins in the possession of <fen>Exchanger_2</fen>.
The items which change possession between the <fen>Exchangers</fen>.
This role identifies the time when the exchange takes place.
This role identifies the place where the exchange occurs.
The entity which blocks the <fen>Eclipsed</fen> entity from view.
The entity which is blocked from view.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person who has placed the <fen>Theme</fen> in the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the object that is kept in a <fen>Location</fen> by the <fen>Agent</fen>
The location where the <fen>Theme</fen> is kept. Some, though not all, LUs in this frame incorporate this FE.
<fen>Time</fen> is the time period during which the <fen>Theme</fen> is stored.
The <fen>Place</fen> indicates where the Storing occurs.
The <fen>Collection</fen> whose <fen>Quantity</fen> is under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Collection</fen> which is under discussion. This role is incorporated by all the lexical units in this frame.
The location in which the <fen>Collection</fen> occurs.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Collection</fen> is in the state of having  a particular <fen>Measure</fen> for the <fen>Quantity</fen>.
The person who has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The entity which the <fen>Agent</fen> possesses for a <fen>Duration</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> has possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The person who is absent from his or her <fen>Activity</fen> for a <fen>Duration</fen> of time.
This role describes the activity or responsiblilities from which the <fen>Person</fen> is taking a temporary leave.
The amount of time the <fen>Person</fen> is absent from his or her <fen>Activity</fen>.  This can also be expressed as a description of a duration, as shown below:
The time at which the leave occurs.
listRoleExamples: The trade <fex>with Cuba</fex> went exactly as planned.
I tucked the pistol between my belt and tunic top (how I wish I had kept it, but I later swapped <fex>it</fex> with a Canadian for some cigarettes.
The organization bought the property in 1999, then swapped it with the BLM <fex>for about 100 parcels in 10 counties ranging in size from one to 920 acres</fex>.
The mists obscured <fex>the top of the tower</fex>.
The majority of specimens were poorly represented, as judged by the small size of mature plants, the immaturity of thalli or scarceness <fex>in occurrence</fex>.
Northern Pike are plentiful <fex>in Perrault Lake</fex>.
<fex>These days</fex> food is plentiful and easy to get and physical activity is no longer a part of daily life.
At all times <fex>the Saxon government</fex> held on to its insistently practiced political tradition.
Once you've got a War Bond, hang on to <fex>it</fex> for the full ten years of its life.
Margerite held on to the key <fex>on Wednesday</fex> until I returned to pick it up.
He will retain <fex>in his heart</fex> the memory of the vast Holocaust.
During his <fex>wife's</fex> absence, Linkworth and his mother had another violent argument.
Such conditions would be likely to lead to absence <fex>from work</fex>.
Dissuaded from resigning, Macmillan took <fex>extended</fex> leave rather than restrain his public utterances.
Columbus took leave of the known world <fex>on 6 September 1492</fex>.
